    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Localization is the process of translating and adapting your app into multiple languages",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and regions. Localize your app to provide access for users who speak a variety of",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "languages, and who download from different App Store territories.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "First, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "internationalize",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " your code with APIs that automatically format and translate",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "strings correctly for the language and region. Then add support for content that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "includes plural nouns and verbs by following language plural rules to increase the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "accuracy of your translations.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Translate-and-adapt-your-app",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Translate and adapt your app",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In Xcode, localization refers specifically to the set of resources for a specific",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "language and region that you support.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You add a localization to your project and select the resources you want to include",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for that language and region. Export the localization and send the files to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "localizers",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": ",",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "who translate the user-facing text and adapt resources for particular cultures and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "regions. Finally, you import the localized files and test the app in that language",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and region directly in Xcode.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you release a localized version of your app, you can also localize the App Store",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "information in App Store Connect for the specific territories where you offer your",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "app.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For other localization tips, tools, and resources, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/localization/",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "In Xcode 15 and later, string catalogs are the recommended way to localize strings. In earlier versions of Xcode, use strings and ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "stringsdict",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " files. For more information about string catalogs, see ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.Xcode/documentation/Xcode/localizing-and-varying-text-with-a-string-catalog",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
